</P>
<P>
   They have a tendency to move rapidly between rage and
contemplation, political folly and eternal friendship that might be
a characteristic of the Gulf Arabs rather than the Levant.
</P>
<P>
   But Hussein's family does, indeed, come from the Gulf, from the
province of Hejaz, and it was his great-grandfather (also Hussein)
whom the Ottomans named as emir, sheriff of the holy Muslim city of
Mecca.
</P>
<P>
