<HEADLINE>
CLINTON REQUESTS FUNDS FOR S.M. MOUNTAINS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRETT PAULY  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The health of the Santa Monica Mountains National
Recreation Area got a major booster shot Monday, when President
Clinton requested $5 million to acquire private property for new
parkland in the chain.
</P>
<P>
   In earmarking the largest amount he has ever requested in an
annual federal budget for land acquisition in the Santa Monica
Mountains, Clinton listed it as the budget's fifth most important
land-acquisition objective, said U.S. Congressman Brad Sherman
(D-Woodland Hills).
</P>
<P>
   ``Of course, I knew we would not obtain funding equivalent to
Yellowstone or the Everglades,'' Sherman said in announcing the
news Friday, ``and I am quite gratified to be fifth in the
country.''
</P>
<P>
   The budget now goes to the House of Representative and the
Senate for revisions, Sherman said, and it is uncertain how much of
Clinton's request will be realized in the end.
</P>
<P>
   All of the land puA AT D18006350017 AT D18006350017 AT
D18006350017 AT D18006350017 AT D18006350017 AT D18006350017 AT
D18006350017 AT D18006350017 AT D18006350017 AT D18006350017 G?i%{
</P>
