</P>
<P>
   _ Spring Creek (PO Box 4780, Jackson, Wyo. 83001; 800-443-6139)
is a rustic retreat with monumental views of the Tetons. Set midway
between the town of Jackson and the Jackson Hole Resort, the log
cabin-style rooms have woodburning fireplaces.
</P>
<P>
   The Granary restaurant is where to fuel up before a day on the
steep slopes or dancing two-step at the Million Dollar Cowboy Bar.
Rates from $190.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (Everett Potter is a New York-based free-lance travel
writer.) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   -0-
</P>
