   OHIO-BOOKBEAT _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Like everyone who needs to write
fiction, Frank Dobson wanted more than to tell a tale. He sought to
address the big picture, to shed some light on the larger issues.
He had a story, born of a real incident back in the '80s. ``I got
the premise from watching a PBS show on rational suicide,'' he
said, in which a woman with a terminal illness planned her death.
It was a premise on which could be draped all sorts of issues; so
Dobson started to work. A profile of the local author. (Dempsey,
Dayton Daily News) MOVED TUESDAY.
</P>
