   MILNER-ON-BOOKS _ LUFKIN, Texas _ The headline over the New York
World's review of the brand new novel April 12, 1925, was: ``F.
Scott Fitzgerald's Latest a Dud.'' It referred to ``The Great
Gatsby.'' In 1998, though, the short novel ranked No. 2 on a 100
best books list. That just goes to show you never can tell.
(Milner, Lufkin Daily News) MOVED
</P>
