<HEADLINE>
NETWORKS KICK UP A STORM FOR SWEEPS 
</HEADLINE>
   By JOHN CARMAN  
 c.1999, San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   David Hill, the Aussie who runs the Fox network and a couple of
sports appendages for Rupert Murdoch, said it ever so elegantly.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sweeps suck,'' he blurted out during a recent
question-and-answer session with television critics.
</P>
<P>
   That sucking sound begins Thursday, with the start of the
February sweeps. Anyway, hearing no murmurs of dissent, Hill
