<P>
   The New York Times News Service calls your attention to the
following travel features and columns moved during the last week.
</P>
<P>
   For retransmissions of these stories, please call 888-346-9867.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CONSUMER NEWS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-CRUISE-BOS (Undated) _ To cruise or not to cruise, that
is the question. Most people answer negatively. While cruising
seems a very much ``in'' vacation, only about 10 percent of
Americans have cruised. By Jerry Morris.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-NEW-CRUISES-BOS (Undated) _ These are exciting times for
the cruise world. Not only have some grand ships arrived in ports
around the world, but even more cruise options are on the horizon.
By Jerry Morris.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTHWEST-EFFECT-NYT (Warwick, R.I.) _ Nearly three years ago,
an airy new passenger terminal here looked as if it might become a
$210 million boondoggle. Then Southwest Airlines arrived, and the
number of passengers last year was double the total of 1996. What
happened in Rhode Island has happened many times before as
Southwest has expanded beyond Texas. Now, it is about to start
service from Islip on Long Island as it enters New York, the
country's most lucrative travel market and its biggest challenge to
date. By Laurence Zuckerman.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-TECHNOLOGY-NYT (Undated) _ For many travelers, the Web is
becoming as indispensible as a suitcase. By Peter H. Lewis.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-WEBSITES-NYT (Undated) _ A surfer's selection of Web
sites. By L.R. Shannon.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-BARGAINS-NYT (Undated) _ Hot travel bargains. By Janet
Piorko.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-NOISE-NYT (Undated) _ Tuning out plane noise. By David
Cay Johnston. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-TOYS-NYT (Undated) _ High-tech toys, from a laptop alarm
to a pocket-sized minicam. By Terry Trucco.
</P>
<P>
   PRACTICAL-TRAVELER-NYT (Undated) _ Travel agents trying to catch
up with the web. By Betsy Wade.
</P>
<P>
   GERMANY-NOINTEREST (West Palm Beach) _ Despite Germany's public
relations efforts, many Jews are not interested in traveling to the
country.
</P>
<P>
   SKI-OLDER-BOS (Franconia, N.H. ) _ It is more difficult for
someone in middle age to take up a sport that so many have
imprinted in their muscles and nervous systems as children. By Tony
Chamberlain.
</P>
<P>
   SKI-COLUMN-BOS (Undated) _ Of dogs and ski trails and, well, a
bunch of stuff like that. By Tony Chamberlain.
</P>
