specialist says Texas' units are among the worst, most inhumane
he's ever seen. ``The level of despair ... was unparalleled in my
experience,'' says Craig Haney, chairman of the psychology
department at the University of California at Santa Cruz. Lack of
hygiene items, reading material and recreation contribute to the
degrading atmosphere, Haney tells a federal judge. By JOHN W.
GONZALEZ.
