</P>
<P>
   ATLANTA GAS-RATES _ AGL Resources Inc., parent of Atlanta Gas
Light Co., holds its annual shareholder meeting Friday. In an
interview CEO Walter Higgins takes full responsibility for the mess
over the utility's rates and compares the imbroligo to the furor
over the New Coke. (Quinn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   AIRTRAN-LOSS _ AirTran Holdings reported a net loss of $3.0
million, or $0.05 per share, exclusive of a one-time charge, for
the fourth quarter. The company recorded a one-time charge related
to the 737 fleet in the fourth quarter of $27.5. Operating revenues
increased 51.0 percent for the fourth quarter 1998, totaling $105.7
million compared to $70.0 million for the fourth quarter 1997.
(Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ELECTROSOURCE _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Electrosource Inc., the San
Marcos battery maker, received $300,000 from the U.S. Department of
Energy for research into lithium polymer batteries, a
next-generation rechargeable battery technology. (Gallaga, Austin
American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   REALESTATE _ AUSTIN, Texas _ A group of Texas business
executives have partnered with a large Costa Rican real estate
owner to buy the rights to Coldwell Banker Real Estate Corp.
franchises for seven Latin American countries. (Austin
American-Statesman)
</P>
