<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Friday, Feb. 5, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact David Brady at the Daily News, (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   PRINCIPAL-ATTACK (Los Angeles) _ As police worked to solve the
racially motivated attack on an elementary school principal, the
city launched its own investigation and the administrators union
head discussed how pervasive such tensions are at other Los Angeles
schools. By Lisa Van Proyen. (Will move in the ``a'' national and
``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   REAGAN-LEGACY (Simi Valley, Calif.) _ On former President
Reagan's 88th birthday, more than 400 men and women who served
under him gathered at the Ronald Reagan Presidential Library &AMP;
Museum to discuss his continuing legacy. By Phil Davis. (Will move
in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   CHIMP-CHAMP (Los Angeles) _ While visiting the Los Angeles Zoo
to show off some endangered reptiles confiscated from smugglers,
Mayor Richard Riordan joked that he knows who fathered Toshi the
newborn chimp _ a mystery that has baffled the zoo's animal
handlers. By Lisa Weiss. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n''
California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   NEWSPAPER-ACQUISITION (Los Angeles) _ The parent company of the
Los Angeles Daily News and the Los Angeles Times have jointly
acquired California Independent Postal System Marketing Group Inc.,
a Southern California-based provider of alternative distribution
services for advertising preprints. (Will move in the ``a''
national, ``n'' California and ``f'' financial news files.)
</P>
<P>
   MEDAL-BUSTER (Los Angeles) _ A veteran is traveling the country
tracking down people who falsely claim to have been awarded the
Congressional Medal of Honor. By Dennis McCarthy. (Will move in the
``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   WRITERS-DEAL (Los Angeles) _ A group of Hollywood's top
screenwriters have broken through a longstanding financial barrier
by reaching a highly unusual collective agreement under which
Columbia Pictures has agreed to pay them a portion of the profits
of successful movies in addition to their usual writing fees. By
Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   DOLE-EARNINGS (Westlake Village, Calif.) _ Dole Food Co. is
expected to release quarterly earnings on Friday. By Gregory J.
Wilcox. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
