<SLUG> BC-AUSTRIA-HOLOCAUST-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PROPOSAL ADVANCES TO SETTLE HOLOCAUST CLAIMS AGAINST AUSTRIAN
BANKS
</HEADLINE>
  (See also AUSCHWITZ-BANK) 
(DW) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A lawyer for two Austrian banks said Thursday that
the institutions are circulating a proposal that could would settle
Holocaust-era claims against the banks.
</P>
<P>
   An American plaintiffs' lawyer, Edward Fagan of New York, said
in an interview that an agreement in principle had been reached
between himself, some Jewish groups and the Austrian institutions,
Bank Austria and Creditanstalt.
</P>
<P>
   But the Austrian banks' lawyer said that while a settlement
proposal is being circulated, all involved in the litigation had
not yet reviewed it.
</P>
<P>
   Under the proposal, the banks would turn over documents from
World War II to plaintiffs' attorneys and others involved in the
case.
</P>
<P>
   Both the lawyer for the banks and Fagan said earlier reports
that the banks would pay $92 million to settle the claims were
inaccurate.
</P>
</TEXT>
