<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-04 20:23 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2349 &Cx1f; paxxx
u w &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-STATES-SENS-PA     02-04 0614
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STATES-SENS-PA </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;        SANTORUM AND SPECTER WANTED LEWINSKY TO TESTIFY IN
IMPEACHMENT TRIAL
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;     By Lisa Fine  
 &HT;    c. 1999 States News Service  
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON, Feb. 4 -- Pennsylvania Senators Arlen Specter and
Rick Santorum will have to settle for videotaped testimony of
Monica Lewinsky in President Clinton's impeachment trial.
</P>
<P>
   Despite the preferences of Republicans Specter and Santorum, the
Senate voted 70-30 against having Lewinsky called as a live witness
before the Senate.
</P>
<P>
   Once the trial started, Specter vowed not to speak publicly
about it. But before that, he had called for a full trial with
witnesses. On Thursday, Specter voted to have Lewinsky testify.
</P>
<P>
   Santorum said the trial will lose an important dynamic by not
having live testimony. By not being able to judge Lewinsky's
demeanor during testimony, Santorum said, senators will not be able
to assess her credibility.
</P>
<P>
   ``People have been saying how reluctant Monica Lewinsky was in
saying anything bad about the president. Well, if that is apparent,
and she is a live witness -- a reluctant witness -- anything she
says that is negative will have more credibility,'' he explained.
</P>
<P>
   Santorum said videotaped testimony does not offer as complete a
picture as live testimony.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's like a camera focusing on the puck in a hockey game,''
Santorum said. ``You'd see 90 percent of the game focusing in on
the puck, but you'd miss the interaction of the players and other
key parts of the game.''
</P>
<P>
   Santorum said he did not think his 25 Republican colleagues were
disloyal for joining Democrats in voting against the motion.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it shows that our party is the less political one in
all of this,'' Santorum said. ``It shows everyone is making up his
own mind.'' On Saturday, senators will view videotaped depositions
of the former White House intern, Clinton confidante Vernon Jordan
and White House aide Sidney Blumenthal.
</P>
<P>
   As it is becoming clear the requisite 67 senators will not vote
to remove President Clinton from office, some senators are seeking
alternatives to express their disapproval with his behavior.
</P>
<P>
   But momentum is dying for a ``finding of fact'' resolution which
had been pushed by some Republicans. The proposal would have
accused Clinton of perjury and obstructing justice, but would not
have removed him from office.
</P>
<P>
   Santorum said he opposes anything short of a verdict.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think we should stick to the script our founding fathers
intended for conviction or acquittal,'' Santorum said.
</P>
<P>
   Republican leaders said the trial is on track for a final vote
by Feb 12.
</P>
<P>
   Santorum does not think the trial has derailed the Senate from
doing legislation.
</P>
<P>
   ``My days are longer and I'm doing more work on legislation
since I'm here,'' Santorum said. ``I think we are getting more
done, instead of being on recess like the House.''
</P>
<P>
   Santorum said his office has been flooded with calls from
constituents who want to make their opinion known, but he will not
vote based on popular opinion.
</P>
<P>
   ``The public doesn't sit in the jury box,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   But the public will render the final verdict on Santorum.
</P>
<P>
   Political observers say Santorum and other senators who are up
for reelection in 2000 are made vulnerable by how they handle
themselves in the impeachment trial. They say Santorum is in a
difficult position because Pennsylvania elected Clinton twice.
</P>
<P>
   Santorum said he doesn't think about politics.
</P>
<P>
   ``Frankly, it doesn't have an impact on me at all,'' Santorum
said. ``I have to work through what my decision is on each article.
If I do that and I'm honest, I've done my job. The politics of this
are simply not important.''
</P>
</TEXT>
