<P>
   SCOUTING REPORT: HAWKS VS. CAVS
</P>
<P>
   _ Where: The Georgia Dome.
</P>
<P>
   _ When: 7:30 p.m. today.
</P>
<P>
   _ TV; radio: WATL; WSB-750 AM.
</P>
<P>
   _ Series history: The Hawks have dominated while the Cavaliers
rebuilt with young players, sweeping four games last season. Over
the past three seasons, the Hawks are 10-2 against Cleveland,
although four of the last seven victories have been by five points
or fewer.
</P>
<P>
   _ Tickets: Advance sale of 14,400; all tickets up to $35 are $10
tonight and Saturday against the Nets.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cleveland update: The Cavs made only one important roster
change, re-signing small forward Johnny Newman, who last played for
them as a rookie in 1987. On the downside is power forward Shawn
Kemp's publicized weight problem, although he has slimmed down from
his reporting weight of 303. Guard Bob Sura is slowed by a
right-ankle problem after surgery.
</P>
<P>
   _ The starters: Atlanta _ PF Alan Henderson (6-9), SF LaPhonso
Ellis (6-8), C Dikembe Mutombo (7-2), SG Steve Smith (6-8), PG
Mookie Blaylock (6-1); Cleveland _ PF Shawn Kemp (6-10), SF Cedric
Henderson (6-7); C Zydrunas Ilgauskas (7-3); SG Wesley Person
(6-6), PG Brevin Knight (5-10).
</P>
<P>
   _ Injuries: Atlanta _ center Scot Pollard (flu) is on the
five-game injured list; Cleveland _ forward Ryan Stack (rehab,
broken right hand) is on the injured list.
</P>
