<SLUG> BC-RAC-DAYTONA-ADVANCE05-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Ford teams mounting challenge to Gordon
 &HT;    By Mark Schlabach
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ The race to catch Jeff Gordon and his
Chevrolet begins Saturday when the 1999 NASCAR Winston Cup season
officially begins with qualifying for the Feb. 14 Daytona 500.
</P>
<P>
   While Gordon, who will be shooting for his third points
championship in a row, is obviously the driver in front, veteran
Rusty Wallace and some of the other Ford teams posted some of the
fastest speeds at Daytona testing last month.
</P>
<P>
   In fact, Fords accounted for eight of the top 15 laps in
testing. Wallace, 42, registered the top lap at 193.129 mph, which
would have been good enough to win the pole in last year's Daytona
500.
</P>
<P>
   Gordon was second in testing at 192.452, and Kyle Petty was
third at 192.341 in the No. 44 Pontiac.
</P>
<P>
   Bobby Labonte won last year's pole for the race at 192.415.
</P>
<P>
   ``When we saw those numbers (last month) we were pretty
shocked,'' Gordon said. ``When you get down (there) and put
NASCAR's restrictor plate on and go through inspection, things
change a little bit. If they can put those numbers out there then,
they can have the pole.''
</P>
<P>
   Qualifying for the 500 field begins at 12:30 p.m. Saturday. The
first round determines only the two drivers on the front row, the
pole and outside pole. The other drivers can stand on their speeds
from Saturday's round or run in second- or third-round qualifying
on Monday and Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The laps from Monday and Tuesday are used to determine
positioning for Thursday's 125-mile qualifying races. The 125s will
determine the Nos. 3-30 spots in the race lineup.
</P>
<P>
   The final 13 drivers in the 500 field will come from those with
the six best speeds who hadn't qualified for the race, and
provisional starters based on last year's car-owner standings
points.
</P>
<P>
   DAYTONA 500 QUALIFYING
</P>
<P>
   _ What: Positions 1 and 2
</P>
<P>
   _ When: 12:30 p.m. Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   _ Where: Daytona International Speedway, Daytona Beach, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   _ Additional qualifying: Monday and Tuesday to set positions for
Thursday's 125-mile races, which determine positions 3-30 in the
500 on Feb. 14.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
