Jeff Van Gundy clinging to the leg of the Miami Heat center Alonzo
Mourning last April, allowing himself to be dragged around the
floor like a rodeo clown. Over the last three years, Van Gundy has
been his players' tireless protector and defender through flagrant
fouls, fights and suspensions. With the reputation Van Gundy has
constructed, it is no wonder that Latrell Sprewell, upon his
introduction as a Knick, referred to Van Gundy as a ``player's
