who won the Pulitzer prize for drama last year, was once rejected
by the Yale School of Drama and also turned away by the prestigious
Eugene O'Neill Playwrights Conference - 12 times. The play for
which she won the Pulitzer, ``How I Learned to Drive,'' about the
incestuous relationship between a girl and her uncle, had a
successful run Off Broadway and was the most produced new play in
America last year, with 26 regional productions. (Sara Krulwich/New
