<SLUG> BC-BKL-MERCURY-ASST.-COACH-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
VETERAN COACH LANDA JOINS MERCURY STAFF 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By JEFF METCALFE  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - Howie Landa, who coached Hall of Famer Ann Meyers in
one of the first U.S. professional women's basketball leagues, is
the newest addition to the WNBA runner-up Mercury's coaching staff.
</P>
<P>
   The 67-year-old Landa will bring more than 40 years of men's and
women's pro and college coaching experience. He joins third-year
Coach-General Manager Cheryl Miller and Carrie Graf, the Australian
Women's National Team assistant coach who returns for a second year
with the Mercury.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm real excited because Howie's knowledge is not surpassed by
anyone in the league,'' Mercury Vice President Seth Sulka said.
``He knows basketball and how to teach and coach. He's a great
addition.''
</P>
<P>
   Landa replaces Kathy Anderson, who replaced the lone 1997
assistant, Steve Smith, now an assistant with the Detroit Shock.
</P>
<P>
   Landa was coach of the New Jersey Gems, which featured Meyers,
of the Women's Basketball League in the early 1980s.
</P>
<P>
   His other coaching stops included Allentown Jets (1972-73) of
the Eastern Pro League, Brill (1974-75) of the Italian League,
Mercer County (N.J.) Community College and the University of
Nevada-Las Vegas. He was the UNLV men's assistant in 1988-89 and
1994-95, a stint that included seven games as interim head coach in
place of Tim Grgurich, and women's assistant from 1989-93.
</P>
<P>
   Now a noted basketball clinician, Landa first earned national
recognition in 1953 as leading scorer for the Lebanon Valley Seven
Dwarfs. Then with an enrollment of 425 and no player taller than
6-foot-1, Lebanon Valley is the smallest school ever to play in the
NCAA Tournament, beating Fordham before losing to eventual Final
Four qualifier Louisiana State.
</P>
<P>
   Next up for the Mercury is announcement of its 32-game schedule,
expected next week. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-04-99 2322EST &QL; 
